```

**Expected Behavior**:

The nullable annotation should be consistently expected (or not) regardless of whether a parameter type happens to be an array.

**Actual Behavior**:

Array parameter types emit a C# warning when the nullable annotation is included, but no other types do (that I've noticed).
Also worth noting: the completion list that helps me write the cref in the first place adds the nullable annotation, so the completion list provides text that ends up producing this compiler warning.

